<span class="displaytext">chicago, il - below is a statement from senator (candidate full) on washington mutual <p>"the government-brokered sale of washington mutual is the latest sign of the perilous situation facing our financial system and our economy. although americans with deposits at washington mutual should rest assured that they are safe under this arrangement, the failures of our financial institutions threaten economic instability, jobs, and the incomes of american families. this is a time to rise above politics for the good of the country. we cannot risk an economic catastrophe. this is not a (PARTY NAME) problem or a (PARTY NAME) problem - this is an american problem. now, we must find an american solution," said senator (candidate full).</p></span>



